---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import portrait from '../assets/portrait.png';

// TODO(Guilherme): review this drafted story — correct anything that doesn't
// sound like you.
const beliefs = [
  'Ship things that work, then make them elegant',
  'AI is a tool for leverage, not a magic wand',
  'The best engineers never stop being students',
];
---

<section class="section" id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head" data-reveal>
      <span class="index">02</span>
      <h2>About</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="portrait card" data-reveal>
        <Image src={portrait} alt="Portrait of Guilherme Frazão" widths={[340, 680]} sizes="(max-width: 820px) 300px, 340px" />
      </div>

      <div class="story" data-reveal>
        <p>
          I grew up in Abrantes, Portugal, and found my way into software the
          usual way — by being too curious to leave things unexamined. That
          curiosity took me to <strong>NOVA School of Science and Technology</strong> in
          Lisbon for my bachelor's and master's in Computer Science, and to
          <strong>TU Dresden</strong> in Germany for a semester abroad.
        </p>
        <p>
          Along the way I've built and shipped software in three very different
          environments: debugging and extending customer portals at
          <strong>Vodafone</strong>, designing Azure landing zones as a consultant at
          <strong>Unipartner</strong>, and developing product features on a remote,
          international team at <strong>Intapp</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
          Right now, my energy goes into <strong>applied AI</strong> — my master's
          thesis is a retrieval-augmented generation system that lets LLMs work
          with multi-modal data. I care about building AI systems that are
          genuinely useful: grounded, reliable, and shaped around real problems.
        </p>

        <ul class="beliefs">
          {beliefs.map((b) => (
            <li>
              <span class="dot" aria-hidden="true"></span>
              {b}
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  .about-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: minmax(240px, 340px) 1fr;
    gap: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem);
    align-items: start;
  }
  .portrait {
    aspect-ratio: 4 / 5;
    position: sticky;
    top: 6rem;
  }
  .portrait :global(img) {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    object-fit: cover;
    filter: saturate(0.92);
  }
  .story p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1.3rem;
    max-width: 62ch;
  }
  .story strong {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .beliefs {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-top: 2rem;
    display: grid;
    gap: 0.9rem;
  }
  .beliefs li {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.9rem;
    font-family: var(--font-display);
    font-size: var(--step-0);
    color: var(--text);
  }
  .dot {
    flex: none;
    width: 7px;
    height: 7px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--gradient-accent);
  }
  @media (max-width: 820px) {
    .about-grid {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
    .portrait {
      position: static;
      max-width: 300px;
    }
  }
</style>
